PRETORIA, South Africa, January 5, 2017/APO/ --
                                                
                        President Jacob Zuma will tomorrow, on 06 January 2017, host President Brahim Ghali, President of the Saharawi Arab Democratic Republic (SADR), for a Working Visit to the Republic of South Africa at the Sefako M Makgatho Presidential Guest House in Pretoria.



The visit is aimed at deepening and strengthening the already existing good political relations between the two countries, fortified by the strong historical ties dating back from the years of the struggle against colonialism and apartheid.

Details of the working visit are as follows: 

Venue: Sefako M Makgatho Presidential Guest House, Pretoria
Time: 09:00 am
Date: 06 January 2017

We wish to request media attending the working visit to please send their details to Nelson Kgwete on 076 431 3078 or kgweten@dirco.gov.za and Khutjo Sebata on 079Â 898 4621 or Khutjo@presidency.gov.za.